@ads_sharman, IOSH President, will be participating in the @CIPD Coronavirus webinar series: Looking after key workers, on 24 April 2020 at 12:30 BST / 13:30 CET / 3.30PM UAE / 7.30PM SGP. Register here: http://socsi.in/GqqKY #Covid19

Are you an IOSH member who has adversely been affected by #Covid19? You might be eligible for one of our concessionary rates: http://socsi.in/SpxAt. Contact our Customer Service Centre on: +44 (0)116 257 3198 or email: CSC@iosh.com. Read our FAQs here: http://socsi.in/uswyf.

We encourage you to provide coaching to those who require additional support. One way is to ask employees to send photographs to highlight any potential issues or adjustment queries they may have . Read more here: http://socsi.in/ulP0e #Covid19 #toptipsremote #remoteworkers

There’s still time to join us for IOSH’s next free #webinar today at 12:30 BST / 13:30 CET / 3.30PM UAE / 7.30PM SGP. The theme is ‘The role of the OSH professional - supporting your business throughout the Covid-19 crisis’. Sign up here: http://socsi.in/0m7a6. #IOSHCovid19
Have you joined IOSH Mentoring? Share your knowledge and experience with other OSH professionals while growing your skillset. Sign up to become a mentee at http://socsi.in/JECDr #IOSHmentoring

The IOSH Student Member Bursary is available to you as a member benefit to support you as an aspiring OSH professional during these uncertain times. To see if you are eligible to apply, have a look at http://socsi.in/CvPkx #IOSHStudentBursary #Covid19

During this uncertain time, we encourage co-workers to conduct virtual meetings. If you do need to do face-to-face meetings, follow the government’s advice on social distancing. Read here: http://socsi.in/DzhmQ #Covid19 #toptipsremote #remoteworkers

A brilliant new campaign launched this morning, #ourfrontline, with @MindCharity, @samaritans, @hospiceuk and @GiveUsAShout, to bring much-needed mental health support and resources to #keyworkers tackling #COVID19 - find out more

Join us on Thursday 23 April at 12.30PM BST for our free #webinar. It will provide an insight into the role of the OSH professional in the current climate, and looks forward to a post Covid-19 world. http://socsi.in/bHu3Z #IOSHCovid19

It’s #IOSH’s official 75th anniversary today and, although we’ve postponed our formal celebrations until next year, our President, Dr Andrew Sharman, has posted a great Birthday gift: a greetings video with a tune!
Are you struggling financially due to #Covid19? Have you been an IOSH member for three years? You may be eligible to apply for the #IOSHBenevolentFund. Read more here: http://socsi.in/TneMz

Are you an IOSH member and have a question about your membership during the #Covid19 pandemic? You can still call or email our Customer Service Centre who will offer the same level of advice and support. Read our FAQs here: http://socsi.in/HoTmL

We encourage you to keep in regular contact with employees as they may feel isolated and lonely working at home. You can do this by using a variety of methods: teleconference, email, telephone, email or WhatsApp. Read here: http://socsi.in/Qi1mq #toptipsremote #remoteworkers

An expert panel will address what their biggest challenges are and how they’re addressing them in our free #webinar. Register to take part on 23 April at 12.30PM BST. http://socsi.in/xG0SO #IOSHCovid19

Tomorrow is IOSH’s 75th anniversary. Due to the #Covid19 pandemic, we have decided to postpone planned activities to mark this milestone until 2021. Read here for our reasoning in full: http://socsi.in/RLVMp
